menu "UWA Jetski - Briterencoder CAN"

    config ENCODER_DEVICE_ID
        int "Encoder CAN device address (node ID)"
        default 1
        range 1 255
        help
            CAN node address of the Briterencoder. This is also the CAN frame
            identifier used by the encoder. Factory default is 1.

    config ENCODER_RESOLUTION
        int "Encoder single-turn resolution (counts per revolution)"
        default 1024
        range 64 65536
        help
            Number of encoder counts per full revolution. Common values:
            1024 (10-bit), 4096 (12-bit), 16384 (14-bit).
            Must match the physical encoder model.

    config ENCODER_AUTO_PERIOD_MS
        int "Encoder auto-return period (ms)"
        default 20
        range 1 1000
        help
            How often the encoder sends position frames in auto-return mode.
            20 ms = 50 Hz, matching the 50 Hz control loop.

    config ENCODER_MAX_ANGLE_DEG
        int "Rudder maximum deflection angle (degrees)"
        default 45
        range 5 180
        help
            Physical maximum rudder angle from centre in either direction.
            Used to map encoder angle to a 0–100% rudder percentage for the
            control loop (50% = centre).

endmenu
